Editing File
---------------
https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E19683-01/806-7612/editorvi-tbl-83/index.html

Moving to Start or End of Line
Press ^ to move the cursor to the start of the current line.
Press $ to move the cursor to the end of the current line.
l key to move to the right side.
h key to move to the left side.
k key to move upside in the file.
j key to move downside in the file.
Press H (“high”) to move the cursor to the top of the screen.
Press L (“low”) to move the cursor to the bottom of the screen.
Press M (“middle”) to move the cursor to the middle of the screen.

press Esc and finally two keys Shift + ZZ together to come out of the file completely.
find and replace = :$s/old/new/g or $s/old/new/cg (confirm)
to search word from top to bottom = /word to contiue with search \n it go to next line
to search word from bottom to top = ?word to contiue with search \n it go to next line
to copy complete line = esc+yy
to paste =esc+p
to delete current line esc+DD to delete current word esc+dw
==================================
read statement
#!/bin/bash
echo "enter your name:"
read name
echo "hello,$name"
---------------
wild card : matches any string or group of charachters
ls * ->to show all the files, ls *a -->firstname is starts with letter a 
